    Scope and Contents
COAL MINING AND UNION ACTIVITIES PROJECT
Small, editor of the Harrisburg Daily Register, recalls mine wars and violence between the Progressive Miners and United Mine Workers in Illinois; the Sahara Coal Company in Saline County; and descriptions of the UMW and PMA. Also recalls gangsters and gang violence in the 1930's.1 tape, 63 mins., 26 pp.
Interview by Rex Rhodes, 1972
